        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer18387787" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2669861060939376011">I really enjoyed &quot;The Day of the Locusts.&quot; Any book that features a drunk dwarf in the first ten pages is ok by me. His clean, realistic style, crossing into deep psychological insight, makes me wonder what else Mr. West would have written had he not bit the bullet so early.<br/><br/>&quot;Miss Lonelyhearts&quot; didn&apos;t do as much for me, I must admit. Maybe I should read it again. Anyway, add Mr. West to the list of &quot;why isn&apos;t this guy more popular?&quot; authors. Mr. West, meet Mr. Sherwood Anderson.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText2669861060939376011" style="display:none">I really enjoyed "The Day of the Locusts." Any book that features a drunk dwarf in the first ten pages is ok by me. His clean, realistic style, crossing into deep psychological insight, makes me wonder what else Mr. West would have written had he not bit the bullet so early.<br /><br />"Miss Lonelyhearts" didn't do as much for me, I must admit. Maybe I should read it again. Anyway, add Mr. West to the list of "why isn't this guy more popular?" authors. Mr. West, meet Mr. Sherwood Anderson.<br /><br /></span>
