    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3347149346" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3347149346" />
    <a title="Matthew Ted" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57003346-matthew-ted"><img alt="Matthew Ted" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1578773686p2/57003346.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3347149346?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matthew Ted" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matthew Ted" href="/user/show/57003346-matthew-ted">Matthew Ted</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099573166" href="/book/show/13536869-the-day-of-the-locust-and-miss-lonelyhearts">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3347149346" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer472372966820505643">I reviewed these two books separately on account of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/250041.Miss_Lonelyhearts' title='Miss Lonelyhearts by Nathanael West' rel='nofollow noopener'>Miss Lonelyhearts</a> being on my 1001 list and needing to go in the shelf without <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/113441.The_Day_of_the_Locust' title='The Day of the Locust by Nathanael West' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Day of the Locust</a>.<br/><br/>Ironically, the latter is better, and not on the 1001. <br/><br/>Miss Lonelyhearts: <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3303255726' rel='nofollow noopener'>Review here.</a><br/>The Day of the Locust: <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3303278082' rel='nofollow noopener'>Review here.</a><br/><br/>Read and despair: wistful, sad, oddly violent, broken dreams and bizarre characters. </span>
  <span id="freeText472372966820505643" style="display:none">I reviewed these two books separately on account of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/250041.Miss_Lonelyhearts" title="Miss Lonelyhearts by Nathanael West" rel="nofollow noopener">Miss Lonelyhearts</a> being on my 1001 list and needing to go in the shelf without <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/113441.The_Day_of_the_Locust" title="The Day of the Locust by Nathanael West" rel="nofollow noopener">The Day of the Locust</a>.<br /><br />Ironically, the latter is better, and not on the 1001. <br /><br />Miss Lonelyhearts: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3303255726" rel="nofollow noopener">Review here.</a><br />The Day of the Locust: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3303278082" rel="nofollow noopener">Review here.</a><br /><br />Read and despair: wistful, sad, oddly violent, broken dreams and bizarre characters. </span>
  <a data-text-id="472372966820505643" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


