<div id="review_10470657" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10470657" />
    <a title="Saxon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/217922-saxon"><img alt="Saxon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1265440874p2/217922.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/10470657?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Saxon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Saxon" href="/user/show/217922-saxon">Saxon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">you.</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10470657" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8098544100339895024">Well, I have to say that I am sorely disappointed that I have to part with these two novellas. I feel like I am going through a bad breakup. Fitting? Perhaps. I have a professor/novelist friend from Denmark who considers books like lovers. If you are reading a book the first question he will ask you is, &quot;So...was it a good lover? did it make you breakfast in the morning and rub your back or did it leave a note and take your money out of your wallet?&quot; West was good. real good. taught me a few thi</span>
  <span id="freeText8098544100339895024" style="display:none">Well, I have to say that I am sorely disappointed that I have to part with these two novellas. I feel like I am going through a bad breakup. Fitting? Perhaps. I have a professor/novelist friend from Denmark who considers books like lovers. If you are reading a book the first question he will ask you is, "So...was it a good lover? did it make you breakfast in the morning and rub your back or did it leave a note and take your money out of your wallet?" West was good. real good. taught me a few things and left me in need of a shower. I called into work just to get some more. <br /><br />West's writing is simple but creatively imaginative. He is definitely in the school of American fiction but does it with a wit and sharp examination of American society that is wholly his own. I've been reading many plays from this era and it makes them seem elementary compared to West. Funny, dark, bleak, bizarre and yet seemingly fitting...ugh...buy me a beer and i'll tell you more about it.<br /><br />just read him.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8098544100339895024" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


